label.value: AOTU neuron of the dopaminergic PAL cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PAL cluster. It has a major arborization site in the anterior optic tubercle.

label.value: LH-SMP neuron of the dopaminergic PAL cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PAL cluster. It has major arborization sites in the lateral horn and the superior medial protocerebrum.

label.value: SMP-PED neuron of the dopaminergic PPL1 cluster

value.value: MB-SV neuron that has terminals in the mushroom body pedunculus and the superior medial protocerebrum, in addition to the area surrounding the vertical lobe.

label.value: SMP-gamma neuron of the dopaminergic PPL1 cluster

value.value: Unilateral MB-SV neuron that has terminals in the mushroom body gamma lobe and the superior medial protocerebrum, in addition to the area surrounding the vertical lobe (Xie et al., 2018). It develops from the larval OAN-e1 cell (Truman et al., 2023).

definition.value: PPL1-SMP in Truman et al. (2023) judged to correspond to SMP-gamma in Xie et al. (2018) based on figures and descriptions in papers and FlyCircuit 3D image (TH-F-000018) in Virtual Fly Brain - unilateral and innervation mainly in posterior crepine and SMP, with only small amount in gamma lobe - cp231004.

label.value: bSMP-gamma neuron of the dopaminergic PPL1 cluster

value.value: Bilateral MB-SV neuron that has terminals in the mushroom body gamma lobe and the superior medial protocerebrum, in addition to the area surrounding the vertical lobe.

label.value: SLP neuron of the dopaminergic PPL2ab cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPL2ab cluster. It has a major arborization site in the superior lateral protocerebrum (Mao and Davis, 2009; Xie et al., 2018). It does not innervate the mushroom body calyx (Mao and Davis, 2009). It is GABAergic (Dolan et al., 2019).

definition.value: Mapped to hemibrain PPL203 based on lack of calyx innervation, SLP innervation and comparison to Fig 6 of Mao and Davis (2009). PPL203 stated to correspond to PPL2ab-PN1 of Dolan et al. (2019) in neuprint (neuprint.janelia.org) hemibrain 1.1 data.

label.value: vLH-CA neuron of the dopaminergic PPL2ab cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPL2ab cluster. Its major arborization sites are in the ventral lateral horn and the mushroom body calyx (Mao and Davis, 2009; Xie et al., 2018). The primary neurite extends dorsally and one branch innervates the calyx (Mao and Davis, 2009). A second branch innervates the a small part of adjacent posterior inferior lateral protocerebrum and the ventral portion of the lateral horn (Mao and Davis, 2009). A third branch projects medially and innervates the middle inferior medial protocerebrum (Mao and Davis, 2009).

definition.value: Identified in Mao and Davis (2009), who claim this is the MB-C1 neuron from Tanaka et al (2008) - FBrf0205263, but the two are listed as distinct in Aso et al. (2014) - FBrf0227179. Mapped to hemibrain PPL202 based on ventral innervation of lateral horn and comparison to Fig 6 of Mao and Davis (2009). Schlegel et al. (2021) - FBrf0249560 map PPL202 to LHCENT7, but in hemibrain notes LHCENT7 is mapped to PPL201.

label.value: LH-CA neuron of the dopaminergic PPL2ab cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPL2ab cluster. It has major arborization sites in the lateral horn, the entire mushroom body calyx and the middle superior protocerebrum (Mao and Davis, 2009; Xie et al., 2018).

definition.value: Mapped to hemibrain PPL201 based on full innervation of lateral horn and comparison to Fig 6 of Mao and Davis (2009). LHCENT7 and PV1a1 are synonyms of PPL201 in neuprint (neuprint.janelia.org) hemibrain 1.1 data, but Schlegel et al. (2021) - FBrf0249560 map LHCENT7 to PPL202.

label.value: ALT neuron of the dopaminergic PPL2ab cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPL2ab cluster. It passes close to the antennal lobe tract and is distinct from the ALT-PLPC neuron.

label.value: ALT-PLPC neuron of the dopaminergic PPL2ab cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPL2ab cluster. It passes close to the antennal lobe tract and the posterior posteriolateral protocerebral commissure.

label.value: VES-LO neuron of the dopaminergic PPL2c cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPL2c cluster. It has major arborization sites in the vest and the lobula.

label.value: VES neuron of the dopaminergic PPL2c cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPL2c cluster. It has a major arborization site in the vest and is distinct from the VES-LO neuron.

label.value: VLP-SAD neuron of the dopaminergic PPM2 cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPM2 cluster. It has major arborization sites in the ventrolateral protocerebrum and the saddle.

label.value: VLP neuron of the dopaminergic PPM2 cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPM2 cluster. It has a major arborization site in the ventrolateral protocerebrum and is distinct from the other VLP-innervating PPM2 neurons.

label.value: WED neuron of the dopaminergic PPM2 cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPM2 cluster. It has a major arborization site in the wedge. There are two of these cells per hemisphere.

label.value: VLP-AMMC neuron of the dopaminergic PPM2 cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPM2 cluster. It has major arborization sites in the ventrolateral protocerebrum and the antennal mechanosensory and motor center.

label.value: LAL-SEG neuron of the dopaminergic PPM2 cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPM2 cluster. It has major arborization sites in the lateral accessory lobe and the subesophageal zone.

label.value: LAL neuron of the dopaminergic PPM2 cluster

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with a cell body in the PPM2 cluster. It has a major arborization site in the lateral accessory lobe and is distinct from the LAL-SEG neuron.

label.value: adult dopaminergic neuron of gnathal ganglion

value.value: Adult dopaminergic neuron with its cell body in the gnathal ganglion (Marella et al., 2012). The ventral gnathal ganglion has four dopaminergic neurons; a bilateral pair with each neuron arborizing in one half of the subesophageal zone, a relatively anterior unpaired neuron and a relatively posterior unpaired neuron (Marella et al., 2012).

label.value: adult dopaminergic AUM neuron of the gnathal ganglion

value.value: Unpaired dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located anterior to the dopaminergic VUM neuron in the ventral gnathal ganglion of the adult brain. It arborizes in a similar pattern to the dopaminergic VUM neuron in the subesophageal zone, but it also extends beyond this region (Marella et al., 2012).

label.value: adult dopaminergic APM neuron of the gnathal ganglion

value.value: Dopaminergic neuron whose cell body is located in the ventral gnathal ganglion of the adult brain. It arborizes in one half of the subesophageal zone and the antennal lobe (Marella et al., 2012).

label.value: SMP neuron of the dopaminergic PPL1 cluster

value.value: Bilateral MB-SV neuron that has terminals in the superior medial protocerebrum, in addition to the area surrounding the vertical lobe (Xie et al., 2018). It develops from a larval DAN-f1 neuron (Truman et al., 2023).

definition.value: PPL1-bi-SMP in Truman et al. (2023) judged to correspond to SMP in Xie et al. (2018) based on figures and descriptions in papers and FlyCircuit 3D image (TH-M-000039) in Virtual Fly Brain - bilateral and relatively dorsal arbors compared to other PPL1 neurons - cp231004.

label.value: gustatory receptor neuron of the wing

value.value: Sensory neuron of the adult that innervates a curved chemosensory bristle on the anterior wing margin and expresses taste receptors (Amrein and Thorne, 2005). It has presynaptic terminals in the wing neuropil (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

label.value: wing margin taste bristle

value.value: Multiply-innervated, chemosensory bristle of the anterior wing margin (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989). It has a conspicuous pore at its distal end (Palka et al., 1979).

label.value: wing margin mechanosensory bristle

value.value: Bristle of the anterior wing margin that is singly-innervated by the dendrite of a mechanosensory neuron (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

label.value: wing bristle mechanosensory neuron

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron that has a dendrite in a bristle of the wing. It has presynaptic terminals in the wing neuropil (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of leg chordotonal organ

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates a scolopidium of a chordotonal organ in the leg. These neurons have axon terminals in a stratum of the leg neuropil that partially overlaps the terminals of campaniform sensillum neurons and is relatively dorsal compared to the terminals of other somatosensory neurons (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

definition.value: Tsubouchi et al., 2017 have a diagram showing tibial chordotonal receptor neurons, but they do not clearly show these among their example neurons (Lco1N1 and Lco1N2).

label.value: ascending mechanosensory neuron of leg chordotonal organ

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron of the adult that innervates a scolopidium of a chordotonal organ in the leg and ascends to the brain. Different neurons reach different destinations, such as the gnathal ganglion, wedge and anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum.

label.value: non-ascending mechanosensory neuron of leg chordotonal organ

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron of the adult that innervates a scolopidium of a chordotonal organ in the leg and does not ascend to the brain.

label.value: mechanosensory neuron of Wheeler's organ

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron that innervates a scolopidium of Wheeler's organ. These neurons project directly to the prothoracic neuromere and converge with the axon terminals of the leg chordotonal organ neurons in the leg neuropil (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

label.value: wing campaniform sensillum

value.value: Campaniform sensillum of the wing.

label.value: sensory neuron of wing campaniform sensillum

value.value: Neuron that has a dendrite in a campaniform sensillum of the wing. They are located on the dorsal and ventral surfaces of the wing base and they respond to mechanical stimuli. Their presynaptic terminals are found in the middle and dorsolateral parts of the wing neuropil and some of these neurons also ascend to the dorsal gnathal ganglion (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

label.value: adult abdominal mechanosensory chaeta

value.value: Mechanosensory chaeta found on the surface of the adult abdomen. They are found on the dorsal surface and close to the ventral midline (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

definition.value: Any mechanosensory chaeta of the terminalia are also covered by this term - https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1373-1705.

label.value: adult abdominal mechanosensory chaeta neuron

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron that has a dendrite in a mechanosensory chaeta of the adult abdomen. Its presynaptic terminals are found in the abdominal neuromere, dorsal to those of the abdominal multidendritic neurons (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

label.value: adult thoracic mechanosensory chaeta

value.value: Mechanosensory chaeta found on the surface of the adult thorax (excluding legs, wings and halteres) (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

label.value: adult thoracic mechanosensory chaeta neuron

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron that has a dendrite in a mechanosensory chaeta of the adult thorax (excluding legs, wings and halteres). It projects to a ventral layer within the wing neuropil (Tsubouchi et al., 2017).

label.value: adult multidendritic neuron

value.value: Any multidendritic neuron of the adult.

label.value: larval multidendritic neuron

value.value: Sensory neuron of the larval peripheral nervous system that has multiple dendrites (Bodmer and Jan, 1987). This includes larval dendritic arborization, bipolar dendrite and tracheal dendrite neurons (Bodmer and Jan, 1987).

label.value: adult visual projection neuron

value.value: Neuron that projects from the adult optic lobe to the central brain, conveying information from light stimuli.

label.value: visual projection neuron

value.value: Neuron that projects from the optic lobe to the central brain, conveying information from light stimuli.

label.value: terminal filament cell

value.value: Somatic cell of the anterior part of the terminal filament that does not contact the germline stem cells.

definition.value: They express en and weak LamC, but unlike cap cells they lack tj expression (Panchal et al., 2017).

label.value: larval optic neuropil

value.value: Small neuropil compartment of the larval optic lobe that contains the axons of photoreceptors. It is the first center for visual processing in the larval brain. It is largely surrounded by the outer optic anlage at earlier developmental stages and becomes sandwiched between the developing proximal medulla and the inner optic anlage by third instar. It is incorporated into the adult optic lobe as the accessory medulla.

label.value: distal larval optic neuropil

value.value: Distal region of the larval optic neuropil, closest to the entry point of the Bolwig nerve. It contains the terminals of the Rh6 photoreceptors.

definition.value: The distal LON in Sprecher et al., 2011 (FBrf0215208) also included the intermediate LON; these were separated in Larderet et al., 2017.

label.value: intermediate larval optic neuropil

value.value: Intermediate region of the larval optic neuropil, between the distal and proximal LON regions. It contains the terminals of the Rh5 photoreceptors.

definition.value: The distal LON in Sprecher et al., 2011 (FBrf0215208) also included the intermediate LON; these were separated in Larderet et al., 2017.

label.value: proximal larval optic neuropil

value.value: Proximal region of the larval optic neuropil, closest to the brain. It does not contain terminals of any photoreceptors.

label.value: adult lateral horn neuron

value.value: Adult neuron that has dendritic arbors in the lateral horn (including local neurons). Many of these receive olfactory input from antennal lobe projection neurons.

definition.value: In contrast to previous usage, Dolan et al. (2019) (FBrf0242477) use 'lateral horn neuron' to refer to any neuron associated with the lateral horn, including input neurons. This class only includes neurons with dendritic arborizations in the lateral horn.

label.value: adult abdominal multidendritic neuron

value.value: Mechanosensory multidendritic neuron that innervates the adult abdomen. These neurons extend dendrites under the dorsal and lateral body walls. Three innervate the dorsal region and two innervate the ventral region. Their axons project to a ventral region in the abdominal neuromere.

label.value: haltere campaniform sensillum

value.value: Any campaniform sensillum that is part of the haltere. There are four groups of these, found on the dorsal and ventral sides of the proximal and middle parts.

label.value: sensory neuron of haltere campaniform sensillum

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in a campaniform sensillum of the haltere. Their axons terminate in the haltere neuropil and they respond to mechanical stimuli. Some axon terminals reach the ventral gnathal ganglion.

definition.value: Some of these may express fruitless - Yu et al. (2010) - FBrf0211884 believe their 'HAN' neurons innervate haltere campaniform sensilla.

label.value: sensory neuron of haltere capitellum trichoid sensillum

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in a capitellum trichoid sensillum.

definition.value: Some of these may be octopaminergic based on Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Pauls et al., 2018 - FBrf0240407).
